headline: Why Super Micro (SMCI) Shares Are Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of server solutions provider Super Micro (NASDAQ:SMCI) fell 3.8% in the morning session after the Trump administration's announcement of new global tariffs, reignited trade policy uncertainty. The move came swiftly after the Supreme Court ruled the previous week that the president could not use the International Emergency Economic Powers Act (IEEPA) for such duties, a decision that had initially sent markets higher.
